 been marginal to our accounts of print culture) and excavates the long-forgotten reading practice of cutting printed books. Proposing radical deformations to the meanings of fundamental and apparently simple terms such as "error," "letter," "surface," and "cut," Fleming opens up exciting new pathways into our understanding of writing all told.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 4aCultural Graphology. 4aJacques Derrida. 4abook history. 4adeconstruction. 4aearly modern. 4aliterature. 4aprint. 4apsychoanalysis. 4awriting. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311070422808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2016z978311068860308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226390567423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226390567.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-068860-3  UChP eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070422-8  UChP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles